      • originals

        public static scala.collection.mutable.Map<java.lang.Object,scala.ref.WeakReference<Accumulable<?,?>>> originals()
        This global map holds the original accumulator objects that are created on the driver. It keeps weak references to these objects so that accumulators can be garbage-collected once the RDDs and user-code that reference them are cleaned up. TODO: Don't use a global map; these should be tied to a SparkContext (SPARK-13051).

      • register

        public static void register(Accumulable<?,?> a)
        Register an Accumulable created on the driver such that it can be used on the executors.

        All accumulators registered here can later be used as a container for accumulating partial values across multiple tasks. This is what DAGScheduler does. Note: if an accumulator is registered here, it should also be registered with the active context cleaner for cleanup so as to avoid memory leaks.

        If an Accumulable with the same ID was already registered, this does nothing instead of overwriting it. This happens when we copy accumulators, e.g. when we reconstruct TaskMetrics from accumulator updates.

        Parameters:
        a - (undocumented)
